  "title": "Architectural Coordinator (LTA, 5.5 days)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Assist the team leader in coordinating architectural works, ensuring compliance with design and regulatory requirements.</li>\n  <li>Review drawings, specifications, and technical details, highlighting any discrepancies for resolution.</li>\n  <li>Collaborate with internal teams and manage DAR submissions and approval documentation.</li>\n  <li>Organize and participate in coordination meetings with contractors, LTA, AE, and other stakeholders.</li>\n  <li>Oversee site installations, mock-up inspections, and trade demos to ensure alignment with project standards.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma in Architecture or equivalent</li>\n  <li>At least 3 years of relevant experience with a <strong>main contractor</strong>, having handled <strong>LTA projects.</strong></li>\n  <li>Strong communication and coordination skills with the ability to manage subcontractors effectively.</li>\n  <li>Proficiency in Microsoft Office, <strong>AutoCAD, Revit,</strong> and other relevant software.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you are keen to apply for the position, kindly email your detailed resume in<strong> MS Word </strong>to <strong>hr@recruit-expert.com</strong></p>\n<p>Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>\n<p>For more job opportunities, please visit our website at <a href=\"http://www.recruit-expert.com/\"><strong>www.recruit-expert.com</strong></a></p>\n<p>EA Licence: 19C9701<br>\nRegistration: R21100996</p>",
